SR-410 Chinook Pass: Travelers are advised to use caution near the Hells Crossing Campground area at milepost 81 15 miles east of the Chinook Pass summit where portions of the highway have been damaged due to flooding. A repair project is planned this summer with minor traffic delays. Contact: Jerry Wood Project Engineer 509-577-1859Project Description: This project provides for the improvement of SR 410 by excavating Crushed Surface Base Course in select areas and paving it back with HMA saw cutting edges of roadway that may be unraveling providing temporary striping ditch grading and guideposts. This project is due to be completed late Summer 2020.
